              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/629685-meels?shelf=dragons">dragons</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/629685-meels?shelf=on-my-nook">on-my-nook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/629685-meels?shelf=action">action</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/629685-meels?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/629685-meels?shelf=own-it">own-it</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/629685-meels?shelf=5000-books-for-2019">5000-books-for-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/629685-meels?shelf=read-more-than-once">read-more-than-once</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer884215272" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15490758757344234558">A collection of novellas in the Pernverse. Some rehashing of old stuff, which she sometimes does in this series, and it annoys me. But, not a complete rehash, like Narilka’s story. More like Dolphins of Pern, where there is some parallel and occasional overlap, but a new storyline.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

