  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2687975302" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2687975302" />
    <a title="Kessily Lewel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/81574047-kessily-lewel"><img alt="Kessily Lewel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525368899p2/81574047.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2687975302?book_show_action=true">Jan 24, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kessily Lewel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kessily Lewel" href="/user/show/81574047-kessily-lewel">Kessily Lewel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/81574047-kessily-lewel?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2687975302" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10035028113636503593">Chronicles of Pern: First Fall isn&apos;t a full novel, it&apos;s a collection of five short stories about the early days of Pern, during the first generations after they landed. It&apos;s a snapshot of early history on Pern and also connects to things that happened off-planet. I enjoyed each of these stories, but I think The Second Weyr was my favorite. <br/><br/>The first covers the original survey team who visited Pern and declared it fit to be colonized. Expressing some of the problems they had on their mission and </span>
  <span id="freeText10035028113636503593" style="display:none">Chronicles of Pern: First Fall isn't a full novel, it's a collection of five short stories about the early days of Pern, during the first generations after they landed. It's a snapshot of early history on Pern and also connects to things that happened off-planet. I enjoyed each of these stories, but I think The Second Weyr was my favorite. <br /><br />The first covers the original survey team who visited Pern and declared it fit to be colonized. Expressing some of the problems they had on their mission and why they didn't know about thread.<br /><br />Dolphin's Bell is next and focuses on the evacuation from the main landing site with the help of the enhanced dolphins that had come to Pern with the humans. Over time the humans lose touch with the dolphins and forget they were once partners so in present Pern we've only just begun to interact with them. This allows us to see how helpful they were back then.<br /><br />Ford of Red Hanrahan brings back Sorka's parents. Now that people are getting used to thread it's time to start spreading back out across Pern again. Overcrowding as the population starts to climb means it's time for people to go and claim their stakes again. We watch her parents as they form one of the most important holds. There's a lot of "oooh!! That's why!" when you read this one. <br /><br />Next we have a short story about the first dragon riders, The Second Weyr. This is while Sean and Sorka were still leading them, still in their prime, but there were enough dragons to start spreading out to form new Weyrs. Dragon's breed yearly after they reach maturity so there are a number of generations of dragons already and they take up a lot of space. A new Weyr is essential! But where? And who will lead them? We see some of the later dragonrider traditions being formed here.<br /><br />The last story is a sad one because it reflects on the hard times people faced after the original colony was decimated by thread and then illness. This is years later and the focus is on a small group of survivors, who don't know anyone else survived on the planet. We find out the fate of Kenjo's wife and children when the distress beacon that Ted Tubberman had sent off against orders (Dragonsdawn) is found by a passing exploratory vessel. On the ship is Paul Bendan's nephew who is, of course, interested in his uncle's fate. The roving ort cloud is of scientific interest so they decide to send an away mission to the planet to check things out.<br /><br /> We also find out what happened with Steve Kimmer, who was introduced as a very shady individual back in Dragonsdawn. He doesn't get any better as time goes on, in fact he gets worse. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10035028113636503593" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

